<TITLE> Govt to formulate broadband policy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 30 (bdnews24.com)  Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed has asked for a national broadband policy to make internet services cheaper and more widely available, according to a government statement released on Saturday. At a high-level government meeting on Saturday, Fakhruddin asked the authorities concerned to take steps to cut internet charges and prices of computer and computer accessories. The meeting stressed coordination among the Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Commission, Bangladesh Telecommunications Company Ltd, Bangladesh Submarine Cable Company Ltd, BGCB, and other concerned bodies to develop infrastructure for connection and network. The meeting decided to raise the number of people using broadband internet connections to 30 percent of the population from just one percent at present. Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam, the CA's special assistants MA Malek and M Tamim, Bangladesh Bank governor Salehuddin Ahmed, the post and telecommunications secretary, NBR chairman and BTRC chairman were among those attending the meeting. The chief adviser also asked them to take steps to help internet and broadband service providers secure easy loans from financial institutions. bdnew
